from PIL import Image
import numpy as np

# Load the image
image_path = '/mnt/data/Screenshot 2024-10-11 155518.png'
image = Image.open(image_path)

# Convert the image to RGB
image_rgb = image.convert('RGB')

# Convert the image to an array
image_array = np.array(image_rgb)

# Reshape the array to a list of pixels
pixels = image_array.reshape(-1, 3)

# Get the unique colors
unique_colors = np.unique(pixels, axis=0)

# Convert colors to hex
def rgb_to_hex(rgb):
    return '#{:02x}{:02x}{:02x}'.format(rgb[0], rgb[1], rgb[2])

# Get hex colors
hex_colors = [rgb_to_hex(color) for color in unique_colors]

# Get a sample of colors for display
hex_colors_sample = hex_colors[:10]  # Displaying the first 10 unique colors

hex_colors_sample, len(hex_colors)  # Return sample colors and total unique colors found

# Count occurrences of each color
color_counts = Counter(map(tuple, pixels))

# Get the most common colors

# Convert to hex
most_common_hex = [(rgb_to_hex(color), count) for color, count in most_common_colors]

most_common_hex  # Display the most common colors with their counts
